description:
- Work with Cupertino Engineering team, validates product design for manufacturability and make recommendations for changes, driving for high quality (yield and reliability), cost effective design ;
- Work with Cupertino Engineering team, develops manufacturing process & stations with creative way ;
- Provide guidance and resources to contract manufacturers (CM) partner engineers ;
Support products builds from development stages (Proto, EVT, DVT, PVT ) and ramp/mass productions ;
- Plans, develops and implements procedures for PCBA manufacturing process and quality control in contract manufacturers (CMs);
- Work with cross functional teams, responsible for projects successful transition from engineering to mass productions or from one site to others sites;
- Acts as project leader on a variety of complex projects.

preferred_qualifications:
Solid SMT knowledges & experiences ;
Familiar with process FA equipments/ tool and methodologies ;
General understanding with PCB fabrications and components packages (general IC, SIP, discrete passive components);
Good quality sense and familiar with factory quality control system (IQC, IPQC, SQE, QA/QE) ;
Familiar with industrial standard (for example, IPC - including general SMT cosmetic spec of IPC 610, MSD, rework, ESD ) ;
Good communication & presentation skill ;
Demonstrated strong leadership skill ;
Good team-player and able to work with multiple functional groups ;
Can do attitude and could performing under stress and pressure ;
Other added technical knowledge eg. automation, data science & mechanical design will be an added advantage;
Willing to travel within China and overseas (India, Thailand, etc., ) for projects supports upon request
